49
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,490
who determined he was fine.

50
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:19,170
So he was transferred to our hospital.

51
00:02:20,220 --> 00:02:22,170
Was it Mai Zhihong
who requested the transfer?

52
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:24,300
Siu Lam Psychiatric Center

53
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:25,469
is a high-security facility

54
00:02:25,470 --> 00:02:27,330
with strict rules.

55
00:02:27,590 --> 00:02:28,469
It mainly accepts

56
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:29,890
mentally ill criminals.

57
00:02:30,150 --> 00:02:31,890
But our hospital focuses

58
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,210
on treatment and care.

59
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:34,149
So our place is not

60
00:02:34,150 --> 00:02:35,330
as restrictive.

61
00:02:35,736 --> 00:02:36,700
Could this be a loophole

62
00:02:36,710 --> 00:02:38,010
in the hospital system?

63
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:40,840
We've heard of cases where patients
escape from psychiatric hospitals.

64
00:02:41,540 --> 00:02:42,339
That's very rare

65
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:43,939
these days.

66
00:02:43,940 --> 00:02:45,219
All our wards are equipped

67
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,490
with password locks.

68
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,770
We don't use the regular locks
like we did in the past.

69
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,909
So did every room have its own key

70
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:52,050
back then?

71
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,010
Yes.

72
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:55,610
But doctors and senior nurses

73
00:02:55,660 --> 00:02:57,010
had a master key

74
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:59,520
to open all the doors.

75
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,219
Won't it be dangerous

76
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:02,290
if a patient steals

77
00:03:02,430 --> 00:03:03,400
the master key?

78
00:03:03,660 --> 00:03:04,552
So far,

79
00:03:04,584 --> 00:03:07,170
we've only had one or two instances
where a key went missing.

80
00:03:07,310 --> 00:03:08,499
Our security

81
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:10,240
is on duty 24/7.

82
00:03:10,264 --> 00:03:12,296
So the chances
of a successful escape are small.

83
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:14,909
When Mai Zhihong came

84
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,890
to the hospital,

85
00:03:16,984 --> 00:03:18,360
did you notice anything unusual?

86
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:21,490
He did have
some underlying violent tendencies.

87
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:22,429
Sometimes,

88
00:03:22,430 --> 00:03:23,869
his emotions were unstable.

89
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:25,400
So we'd place him in an isolation room

90
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,770
to let him calm down.

91
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,360
