any good?

188
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:42,000
She's nowhere near
as good as Wong Kakui.

189
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:43,760
I just make do and listen to it.

190
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,760
♪Who is willing to return?♪

191
00:09:46,270 --> 00:09:47,530
Mai Zhihong is nearby.

192
00:09:48,990 --> 00:09:50,000
So?

193
00:09:50,056 --> 00:09:52,390
After spending so many years
in the psychiatric hospital,

194
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,976
it must be hard to get used to it.

195
00:09:54,150 --> 00:09:55,600
How could I not get used to it?

196
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,299
The world itself

197
00:09:57,300 --> 00:09:59,050
is a psychiatric hospital,

198
00:09:59,270 --> 00:10:01,109
and we're all its patients.

199
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,120
What about Bao?

200
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:04,000
So, is Bao used to it?

201
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:06,170
How did you know about Bao?

202
00:10:14,580 --> 00:10:15,450
Mai Zhihong!

203
00:10:17,460 --> 00:10:18,530
What's your problem?

204
00:10:19,110 --> 00:10:19,509
Sorry.

205
00:10:19,510 --> 00:10:20,360
You're nuts!

206
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:21,120
Hello?

207
00:10:21,990 --> 00:10:22,720
Hello?

208
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,170
Hey!

209
00:10:26,180 --> 00:10:27,240
Scumbag.

210
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:37,659
Inspector Zhang,

211
00:10:37,660 --> 00:10:40,690
I've discovered that Chen Jiajie
has a phone that can contact Mai Zhihong.

212
00:10:45,784 --> 00:10:47,440
Why did you call
me back here so urgently?

213
00:10:49,700 --> 00:10:50,760
Hand over the phone.

214
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:54,240
What phone?

215
00:10:55,350 --> 00:10:56,059
The phone

216
00:10:56,060 --> 00:10:57,560
that you used to contact Mai Zhihong.

217
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,290
Why should I hand it over to you?

218
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:00,819
Do you know

219
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:02,330
that as a police officer,

220
00:11:02,660 --> 00:11:03,760
doing that

221
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:05,450
could have serious consequences?

222
00:11:05,780 --> 00:11:07,840
If I hadn't found Mai Zhihong,

223
00:11:08,060 --> 00:11:09,720
you wouldn't even have a lead on him.

224
00:11:09,780 --> 00:11:10,880
No matter what,

225
00:11:12,230 --> 00:11:14,170
we still have to follow the law.

226
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:16,699
It's clearly stated

227
00:11:16,700 --> 00:11:18,632
in the police procedures
how to handle evidence.

228
00:11:18,632 --> 00:11:19,290
You can't just do

229
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:20,170
whatever you want.

230
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:21,840
I know.

231
00:11:22,150 --> 00:11:23,419
I know you want to report me.

232
00:11:23,420 --> 00:11:24,712
But you don't have to be so mean

233
00:11:24,728 --> 00:11:25,650
and take the phone away.

234
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:27,128
All I want is to catch the criminal.

235
00:11:27,176 --> 00:11:28,380
When you work here,

236
00:11:28,390 --> 00:11:29,120
you must...

237
00:11:38,180 --> 00:11:38,960
You...

238
00:11:49,870 --> 00:11:50,810
What did he say?

239
00:11:53,350 --> 00:11:54,229
I'll submit the phone

240
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:55,530
according to proper procedures.

241
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:57,109
Whether

242
00:11:57,110 --> 00:11:58,568
you'll face a disciplinary hearing,

243
00:11:59,750 --> 00:12:00,810
I'll let you know later.

244
00:12:08,230 --> 00:12:08,960
Inspector Zhang.

245
00:12:11,660 --> 00:12:12,840
I just need a word with you.

246
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:21,960
I took the undercover job

247
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:24,650
to get promoted.

248
00:12:25,540 --> 00:12:26,840
If you report me,

249
00:12:27,700 --> 00:12:31,080
my career is ruined and all the work
I've done over the years will be wasted.

250
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,210
So, what do you want me to do?

251
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:37,760
Pretend nothing happened?

252
00:12:38,030 --> 00:12:39,650
I'm not asking you to lie.

253
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,530
How you handle it, what you say,

254
00:12:43,630 --> 00:12:45,170
it's all up to you.

255
00:12:46,300 --> 00:12:47,720
I've always been curious.

256
00:12:48,740 --> 00:12:50,552
You didn't graduate
from the police academy.

257
00:12:50,600 --> 00:12:51,930
But they had you go undercover.

258
00:12:53,110 --> 00:12:54,650
You just arrived in this district.

259
00:12:55,390 --> 00:12:56,450
Yet, you seem

260
00:12:56,660 --> 00:12:58,570
so experienced like a seasoned pro.

261
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:02,509
I pick up a thing or two after spending years
dealing with seasoned pros.

262
00:13:02,510 --> 00:13:03,410
Officer Yao.

263
00:13:09,224 --> 00:13:10,100
I've been suspecting

264
00:13:10,110 --> 00:13:11,840
you aren't Chen Jiajie for a while now.

265
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:14,029
It wasn't until just now

266
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,080
when Mai Zhihong called

267
00:13:15,192 --> 00:13:16,552
and addressed you as Officer Yao

268
00:13:16,696 --> 00:13:18,210
that I was certain of it.

269
00:13:18,700 --> 00:13:20,109
You're the Senior Inspector,

270
00:13:20,110 --> 00:13:21,530
Yang Guangyao,

271
00:13:21,576 --> 00:13:22,880
who went missing 25 years ago.

272
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:37,240
Do you remember

273
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:39,229
what you promised

274
00:13:39,230 --> 00:13:40,050
a little kid

275
00:13:40,660 --> 00:13:41,349
at a crime scene

276
00:13:41,350 --> 00:13:42,210
twenty-five years ago?

277
00:13:46,824 --> 00:13:47,990
- Dad!
- Everyone move back!

278
00:13:48,030 --> 00:13:49,272
Use the umbrella to block them!

279
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:53,600
Kid,

280
00:13:54,510 --> 00:13:55,570
I promise you.

281
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:58,170
I'll catch the murderer
who did this to your dad.

282
00:13:59,060 --> 00:13:59,880
I swear.

283
00:14:03,672 --> 00:14:05,530
- Take him back to the station.
- Yes, sir.

284
00:14:05,540 --> 00:14:06,330
Yes, sir.

285
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,290
If I hadn't met you when I was a kid,

286
00:14:13,420 --> 00:14:14,629
no one would believe this.

287
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,600
I know.

288
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:18,600
I'm confused too.

289
00:14:18,780 --> 00:14:19,989
I know my wife's death

290
00:14:19,990 --> 00:14:21,760
wasn't just a traffic accident.

291
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:23,650
I suspected Mai Zhihong.

292
00:14:23,990 --> 00:14:25,690
But he was at the psychiatric hospital.

293
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:27,570
I couldn't find any leads at all!

294
00:14:32,110 --> 00:14:33,810
I only want to find my daughter.

295
00:14:35,390 --> 00:14:36,389
Have you tried looking

296
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:37,960
for people online?

297
00:14:38,940 --> 00:14:40,330
There are plenty of success stories.

298
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:46,760
There's one person
I've always wanted to look into.

299
00:14:46,940 --> 00:14:48,170
But I'm not sure if it's her.

300
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:50,210
Only you can help me.

301
00:14:52,870 --> 00:14:53,720
Who?

302
00:14:55,060 --> 00:14:57,050
I suspect Kaiqing is my daughter.

303
00:14:59,180 --> 00:15:01,120
Her scar is the same
as my daughter's scar.

304
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:17,779
Inspector Zhang.

305
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:18,570
Sorry to bother you.

306
00:15:19,672 --> 00:15:20,650
It's my first time here.

307
00:15:20,910 --> 00:15:21,760
So here's a gift.

308
00:15:22,350 --> 00:15:23,690
You don't have to bring any gifts.

309
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:25,450
Make yourself at home.

310
00:15:25,870 --> 00:15:26,650
Okay.

311
00:15:27,048 --> 00:15:28,210
Should I take off my shoes?

312
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:30,050
Those are my daddy's slippers.

313
00:15:30,270 --> 00:15:31,760
If you don't mind...

314
00:15:32,390 --> 00:15:33,170
Not at all.

315
00:15:34,420 --> 00:15:35,480
Why do you want to see me?

316
00:15:36,984 --> 00:15:39,368
It's not urgent.
You can get back to what you were doing.

317
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,690
I'll get you a glass of water.

318
00:15:42,940 --> 00:15:43,720
Okay.

319
00:15:44,440 --> 00:15:45,480
That smells delicious.

320
00:15:45,510 --> 00:15:46,410
Are you cooking?

321
00:15:46,940 --> 00:15:47,909
Have you eaten?

322
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:48,720
How about joining me?

323
00:15:48,940 --> 00:15:49,810
Sure.

324
00:15:52,230 --> 00:15:53,050
Thanks.

325
00:15:53,780 --> 00:15:54,810
Sorry

326
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:55,690
about the mess.

327
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:56,840
It's okay.

328
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:03,530
Take a seat.

329
00:16:06,660 --> 00:16:08,059
You even study anatomy at home.

330
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:09,000
That's diligent of you.

331
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:10,290
That belongs to my daddy.

332
00:16:17,592 --> 00:16:19,352
Is that a photo of you
when you were a kid?

333
00:16:21,990 --> 00:16:23,459
It was taken when I was eight.

334
00:16:23,460 --> 00:16:24,240
You look adorable.

335
00:16:26,030 --> 00:16:27,269
Ice hockey.

336
00:16:27,270 --> 00:16:28,410
Canadian Martial Arts?

337
00:16:28,540 --> 00:16:29,840
I've never been to Canada.

338
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:31,760
What is it like over there?

339
00:16:32,616 --> 00:16:33,140
Do you have

340
00:16:33,150 --> 00:16:34,248
any other childhood photos

341
00:16:34,264 --> 00:16:34,840
to show me?

342
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:35,832
I'll bring them to you.

343
00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:36,810
Thanks.

344
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:46,530
These are all part of my dark history.

345
00:16:47,150 --> 00:16:48,290
No one has seen it before.

346
00:16:49,180 --> 00:16:50,080
Thanks.

347
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,000
Yeah?

348
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:01,760
Yes, I'm looking into it now.

349
00:17:03,030 --> 00:17:04,170
I'm at her place.

350
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:07,520
Hello? Hello?

351
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:11,480
What's wrong?

352
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:15,000
Jiajie needs to talk to me
about something.

353
00:17:15,350 --> 00:17:16,520
He's just nearby.

354
00:17:16,910 --> 00:17:18,850
Do you mind if he comes over for a talk?

355
00:17:19,220 --> 00:17:20,610
Can I say I mind?

356
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:30,320
What are you doing here?

357
00:17:31,830 --> 00:17:33,040
Where's Inspector Zhang?

358
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:41,320
A cup of coffee, please.

359
00:17:42,376 --> 00:17:43,832
Did you find any clues on that case?

360
00:17:44,584 --> 00:17:45,960
I've tried my best to look into it.

361
00:17:48,264 --> 00:17:49,520
Here are her childhood photos.

362
00:17:50,350 --> 00:17:51,280
Thanks.

363
00:17:57,790 --> 00:17:59,589
I didn't make Mom upset.

364
00:17:59,590 --> 00:18:01,459
It was you.

365
00:18:01,460 --> 00:18:03,259
Dad, where are you going?

366
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:05,240
I'm scared.

367
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:15,410
Police!

368
00:18:16,550 --> 00:18:17,520
You're under arrest!

369
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:19,720
What are you doing?

370
00:18:19,740 --> 00:18:21,419
You're a police officer, not a thug.

371
00:18:21,420 --> 00:18:22,109
Move aside.

372
00:18:22,110 --> 00:18:23,130
Don't get in people's way.

373
00:18:45,110 --> 00:18:45,850
Kaiqing,

374
00:18:46,390 --> 00:18:47,280
do you need any help?

375
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:48,320
No need.

376
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:53,370
When I look
at your childhood photos in Canada,

377
00:18:54,220 --> 00:18:55,890
your family seemed loving.

378
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,520
Do you think you take after your dad

379
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:02,690
or your mom?

380
00:19:03,740 --> 00:19:04,549
I think

381
00:19:04,550 --> 00:19:05,760
I take after my daddy.

382
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:08,960
He is a coroner.

383
00:19:09,260 --> 00:19:10,259
I became a cop

384
00:19:10,260 --> 00:19:11,690
because of him.

385
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,520
I guess it runs in the blood.

386
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:20,090
Have some coffee.

387
00:19:31,070 --> 00:19:31,960
What's the matter?

388
00:19:32,790 --> 00:19:33,760
Take it.

389
00:19:36,248 --> 00:19:37,800
Didn't you say you want coffee just now?

390
00:19:40,630 --> 00:19:41,699
I have something to do.

391
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:42,650
I have to go.

392
00:19:49,630 --> 00:19:50,800
Why did he want to see you?

393
00:19:51,688 --> 00:19:52,760
Why is he acting so weird?

394
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:55,690
Yeah. He probably went
to investigate something else.

395
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:21,459
One, two, three, four, five,

396
00:20:21,460 --> 00:20:26,170
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

397
00:20:31,110 --> 00:20:33,370
Dad, where are you?

398
00:20:33,660 --> 00:20:35,690
Dad, where are you?

399
00:20:35,700 --> 00:20:36,890
Dad!

400
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,690
Come on out.

401
00:20:50,070 --> 00:20:52,069
Dad, where are you?

402
00:20:52,070 --> 00:20:53,690
Show yourself.

403
00:20:55,630 --> 00:20:56,909
Police, freeze!

404
00:20:56,910 --> 00:20:58,480
Hands over your head.

405
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:02,240
Madam, I didn't do anything wrong.

406
00:21:02,550 --> 00:21:03,389
You're amazing!

407
00:21:03,390 --> 00:21:04,549
You found me!

408
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:05,240
Come.

409
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:07,130
Come up and catch me.

410
00:21:07,660 --> 00:21:09,480
Can you climb up the tree?

411
00:21:09,740 --> 00:21:10,659
Can you catch me?

412
00:21:10,660 --> 00:21:11,850
I can't.

413
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:12,960
Madam,

414
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:14,240
what did I do wrong?

415
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:17,699
Madam, can you tell me

416
00:21:17,700 --> 00:21:18,560
what I did wrong?

417
00:21:19,110 --> 00:21:19,890
Madam.

418
00:21:20,740 --> 00:21:22,720
Madam, did you shower?

419
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:25,760
Drink slowly.

420
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:31,869
That's enough.

421
00:21:31,870 --> 00:21:32,800
Don't drink too much.

422
00:21:33,180 --> 00:21:35,019
Dad, don't smoke.

423
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:36,890
It makes your mouth stink.

424
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:38,419
But why do you act

425
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:39,850
like your mom?

426
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:41,280
Good girl.

427
00:21:42,150 --> 00:21:43,349
I can't control your smoking.

428
00:21:43,350 --> 00:21:45,496
But luckily we have a daughter
to keep you in check.

429
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:50,829
Stop smoking.

430
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:51,960
It's bad for your health.

431
00:21:53,110 --> 00:21:54,170
Yes, madam.

432
00:21:57,350 --> 00:21:58,789
I don't understand

433
00:21:58,790 --> 00:22:00,520
why you would let her find you
so quickly

434
00:22:00,568 --> 00:22:02,280
every time you play hide and seek
with her.

435
00:22:02,350 --> 00:22:03,976
Yet, you call yourself
a great detective.

436
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,939
You didn't see

437
00:22:05,940 --> 00:22:06,936
how panicked she looked

438
00:22:06,968 --> 00:22:08,140
when she called out for me

439
00:22:08,150 --> 00:22:09,170
under the tree.

440
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:10,869
It was heart-wrenching.

441
00:22:10,870 --> 00:22:11,690
I couldn't stand it.

442
00:22:13,740 --> 00:22:15,549
I couldn't find you too.

443
00:22:15,550 --> 00:22:17,170
How do you manage to endure it?

444
00:22:20,424 --> 00:22:22,370
Don't tell me
you're jealous of our daughter.

445
00:22:23,550 --> 00:22:24,960
No, I'm not.

446
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:26,930
I know you're busy
with your investigations.

447
00:22:27,070 --> 00:22:28,890
But you could at least call me.

448
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:30,968
- I promise you that I'll...
- Stop promising me.

449
00:22:30,984 --> 00:22:32,040
You never keep

450
00:22:32,088 --> 00:22:32,960
your promises.

451
00:22:45,420 --> 00:22:46,179
Just go.

452
00:22:46,180 --> 00:22:47,170
Go to work.

453
00:22:47,870 --> 00:22:48,349
Later,

454
00:22:48,350 --> 00:22:49,650
we'll take the taxi back home.

455
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,549
What's so funny?

456
00:22:51,550 --> 00:22:53,410
Because I have an understanding wife.

457
00:22:53,544 --> 00:22:55,384
- Come on. Smile for me.
- You're so annoying.

458
00:22:55,384 --> 00:22:56,680
You look beautiful when you smile.

459
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:57,576
You should smile more.

460
00:23:20,420 --> 00:23:21,800
You said Kaiqing is Xingyao.

461
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,090
How is that possible?

462
00:23:30,550 --> 00:23:32,130
Kaiqing's childhood photos.

463
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,320
Tianming sent it to me.

464
00:23:36,870 --> 00:23:38,040
It really is Xingyao.

465
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:42,280
She doesn't remember anything
from the past.

466
00:23:43,740 --> 00:23:44,610
Wait a minute.

467
00:23:46,550 --> 00:23:47,850
I've met this woman before.

468
00:23:49,790 --> 00:23:50,890
She was that social worker.

469
00:23:55,660 --> 00:23:56,650
Hello, Ms. Ma.

470
00:23:56,790 --> 00:23:57,720
You are...

471
00:23:59,180 --> 00:24:00,149
We probably met

472
00:24:00,150 --> 00:24:01,459
about twenty-two years ago.

473
00:24:01,460 --> 00:24:03,624
When Yang Xingyao had just arrived
at the orphanage,

474
00:24:03,656 --> 00:24:04,520
I visited her.

475
00:24:05,350 --> 00:24:06,720
Xingyao?

476
00:24:07,660 --> 00:24:08,650
I do remember.

477
00:24:09,070 --> 00:24:10,090
Please have a seat.

478
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,259
Her mother had just passed away,

479
00:24:17,260 --> 00:24:18,370
her father had gone missing,

480
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:19,549
and not long after,

481
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:20,968
her grandparents passed away too.

482
00:24:20,980 --> 00:24:22,120
She had no other relatives.

483
00:24:22,168 --> 00:24:23,624
Only you came to see her.

484
00:24:24,390 --> 00:24:26,370
After the accident, she lost her memory.

485
00:24:26,616 --> 00:24:28,000
Did her condition improve later on?

486
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:29,979
She never remembered

487
00:24:29,980 --> 00:24:31,450
who her parents were.

488
00:24:32,420 --> 00:24:33,760
I was worried about her back then.

489
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:34,850
Thankfully,

490
00:24:35,550 --> 00:24:36,499
she was adopted

491
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,090
by a couple who cared deeply for her.

492
00:24:39,420 --> 00:24:40,629
Both of you are still young.

493
00:24:40,630 --> 00:24:41,992
Why do you want to adopt an orphan?

494
00:24:43,180 --> 00:24:43,909
Because my wife

495
00:24:43,910 --> 00:24:46,520
has some health issues
that don't allow her to have children.

496
00:24:46,630 --> 00:24:47,520
But

497
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:49,480
we've always wanted children.

498
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,800
I need to remind you

499
00:24:51,910 --> 00:24:54,090
that adoptive parents
cannot specifically request

500
00:24:54,110 --> 00:24:55,720
to adopt a particular child.

501
00:24:56,310 --> 00:24:58,179
You can only indicate your preferences,

502
00:24:58,180 --> 00:25:00,240
such as age and gender.

503
00:25:00,420 --> 00:25:01,069
Understood.

504
00:25:01,070 --> 00:25:01,890
We'd like

505
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:04,309
to have a girl.

506
00:25:04,310 --> 00:25:05,659
If possible,

507
00:25:05,660 --> 00:25:07,149
around five or six years old

508
00:25:07,150 --> 00:25:11,610
because it's easier
to build a bond at that age.

509
00:25:12,660 --> 00:25:13,890
Also,

510
00:25:13,980 --> 00:25:15,389
we don't mind adopting a child

511
00:25:15,390 --> 00:25:17,576
who might have some emotional
or psychological issues.

512
00:25:18,460 --> 00:25:21,309
That's because my wife studies psychology.

513
00:25:21,310 --> 00:25:23,069
If she can use her expertise

514
00:25:23,070 --> 00:25:24,179
to help the child,

515
00:25:24,180 --> 00:25:27,000
she can grow in a better environment.

516
00:25:47,870 --> 00:25:49,450
Ms. Ma,

517
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,240
look at my arm.

518
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:53,720
What happened to your scar?

519
00:25:53,740 --> 00:25:54,589
Is it gone?

520
00:25:54,590 --> 00:25:55,699
Mommy used magic

521
00:25:55,700 --> 00:25:58,170
to make it disappear.

522
00:25:58,312 --> 00:25:59,800
I took her to get a skin treatment.

523
00:25:59,944 --> 00:26:01,832
Girls tend to care more
about their appearance.

524
00:26:01,832 --> 00:26:03,060
Kaiqing, let's go out and play.

525
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:04,219
Okay, Daddy.

526
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:05,130
Come with me.

527
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:07,320
Kaiqing?

528
00:26:08,500 --> 00:26:09,930
Her name is Chen Kaiqing now.

529
00:26:10,420 --> 00:26:12,170
Since she forgot her past,

530
00:26:12,220 --> 00:26:14,090
we want to give her a new life.

531
00:26:14,220 --> 00:26:15,629
Erase her pain

532
00:26:15,630 --> 00:26:17,090
just like the scar on her arm.

533
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:17,970
Has she ever asked

534
00:26:17,980 --> 00:26:19,090
about the orphanage?

535
00:26:19,500 --> 00:26:20,389
She wasn't here

536
00:26:20,390 --> 00:26:21,259
for very long.

537
00:26:21,260 --> 00:26:23,320
I told her a fire broke out at home.

538
00:26:23,350 --> 00:26:24,370
I was too busy.

539
00:26:24,590 --> 00:26:26,520
So I asked you to look after her.

540
00:26:27,420 --> 00:26:28,210
Also,

541
00:26:28,350 --> 00:26:29,259
we're planning

542
00:26:29,260 --> 00:26:30,520
to move to Canada as a family.

543
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:31,650
Consider it as a new start.

544
00:26:31,656 --> 00:26:32,210
That's great.

545
00:26:32,220 --> 00:26:33,280
This is good.

546
00:26:36,070 --> 00:26:38,800
Kaiqing, come and take a photo with Ms. Ma.

547
00:26:41,550 --> 00:26:43,000
Ready? Look at the camera.

548
00:26:43,460 --> 00:26:44,410
Ready.

549
00:26:44,630 --> 00:26:46,650
Three, two, one.

550
00:26:52,220 --> 00:26:54,000
Coroner Chen
and his wife are decent people.

551
00:26:55,220 --> 00:26:57,090
They did so much to bring joy to Xingyao

552
00:26:57,390 --> 00:26:59,499
and gave her such a warm family
to grow up in.

553
00:26:59,500 --> 00:27:00,410
Don't you agree?

554
00:27:02,310 --> 00:27:03,629
What are you planning to do now?

555
00:27:03,630 --> 00:27:04,984
Are you going to tell Kaiqing?

556
00:27:05,390 --> 00:27:06,320
Forget it.

557
00:27:06,740 --> 00:27:08,760
She's happy with her family now.

558
00:27:09,550 --> 00:27:10,520
No need to tell her.

559
00:27:11,350 --> 00:27:12,589
Even if I told her,

560
00:27:12,590 --> 00:27:13,850
would she believe me?

561
00:27:14,420 --> 00:27:15,450
Not necessarily.

562
00:27:16,020 --> 00:27:17,320
Both of us believe you.

563
00:27:17,740 --> 00:27:19,610
Keeping it to yourself
will only hurt you.

564
00:27:19,630 --> 00:27:21,720
But telling her will hurt
Xingyao even more.

565
00:27:22,020 --> 00:27:23,219
Imagine telling her

566
00:27:23,220 --> 00:27:24,480
she has two fathers

567
00:27:24,980 --> 00:27:26,610
and a traumatic childhood.

568
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:27,890
What good would that do?

569
00:27:28,830 --> 00:27:30,130
Things are fine the way they are.

570
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:31,240
She's happy now.

571
00:27:33,980 --> 00:27:35,320
